question: 納豆
sourceMnemonic: A <kanji>supply</kanji> of <kanji>bean</kanji>s is when you take a bunch of beans, mash them up into a supply, and then ferment them all together to make them into <vocabulary>natto</vocabulary> (also known as <vocabulary>fermented soybeans</vocabulary>).
sourceReadingMnemonic: The reading is an exceptional one. <ja>豆</ja> is okay, and is the on'yomi reading from the kanji. The <ja>納</ja> part is weird though. Instead of being <ja>のう</ja> it's <ja>なっ</ja>. But, if you can remember the meaning of this word, you can just think about how you do <reading>not</reading> (<ja>なっとう</ja>) want to eat <vocabulary>natto</vocabulary>. At least a lot of people don't want to eat it. It's quite the acquired taste.
